## 🔎 Verification Workflow (Downstream Consumers)

Museums, publishers, or educators can verify AethelFrame outputs without running the pipeline.

### CLI Verification
```bash
# Verify embedded C2PA manifest & consent hashes
aethelcli verify render_final.mp4 --verbose
```

**Output:**
```
✅ C2PA Manifest: Valid (Ed25519 signature)
✅ Consent Hash: Matches registry (expires 2028-12-31)
⚠️ Accuracy: 34% speculative → [Speculative Inline] disclaimer applied
✅ Accessibility: WCAG AA compliant (captions synced, AD track present)
📄 Provenance: 3 verified sources, 2 mythic adaptations
```

### SDK Verification (Python)
```python
from aethel_sdk.compliance import ProvenanceVerifier

verifier = ProvenanceVerifier()
report = verifier.scan("render_final.mp4")
print(report.summary())
if not report.is_compliant(policy_level="academic"):
    raise RuntimeError("Artifact fails academic provenance standards")
```

